## Sign 1: Your Team Meetings Feel Like Obligation, Not Momentum

You can feel it the second the call starts. Cameras off. One-word answers. The same voices filling the silence while everyone else counts down to the end.

That's not a communication problem. It's an energy problem. People check out when they don't feel connected to the people around them, and no amount of agenda restructuring fixes that.

Shared physical experience does. When people run a laser maze together, dodge virtual zombies side by side in After the Fall, or battle for points in a challenge room, they build the kind of shorthand that makes real conversation easier. It's hard to stay distant with someone you just watched dive under a laser beam.

