## Sign 2: Departments Work in Silos and Nobody Talks Across Teams

Marketing doesn't know what operations is doing. Sales and product haven't spoken in weeks. Everyone's technically doing their job — but nobody's building anything together.

Siloed teams usually reflect siloed experiences. If your people only interact within their own department, that's the only relationship they'll have.

Mixed-group activities that demand real-time collaboration break that pattern fast. Put your marketing lead and your ops manager on the same VR squad in Arizona Sunshine and watch the silos dissolve in about four minutes.

The key is picking something where people genuinely need each other to succeed. Passive entertainment doesn't do this. Seated trivia nights barely scratch the surface. You need an activity where the outcome actually depends on how well your group communicates under pressure.

